# Purchases – List All Purchases (Admin)
# Smoke tests for GET /purchases.
#
# Admin-only endpoint. Returns a paginated list of all purchases across all users.
# Supports optional filtering by status, user_id, merchant_id, and date range.
# Run the helper login requests below to obtain a fresh token.
#
# Seed data: seeds/all.sql contains at least 6 purchase rows across two users
# (alice and bob) to support pagination and filter smoke tests.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8001/api/v1

# Paste fresh tokens here (use helper login requests below).
# These placeholder values are expired local-dev tokens from seed data — never real credentials.
@adminToken = Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJ1c2VyX2lkIjoiZDlmNGIzYzItNmI1Yy01ZDRlLTdjM2ItNmE1ZTRkM2MyYjFhIiwidXNlcl9yb2xlIjoiYWRtaW4iLCJleHAiOjE3NzMwNTI2Njd9.EOyEXR2AHeB-K52xbDs-uuXkd9qsfU_lt0Hc0QUkhYE
@userToken  = Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJ1c2VyX2lkIjoiYjdlMmMxYTItNGYzYS00ZTJiLTljMWEtOGQyZTNmNGI1YzZkIiwidXNlcl9yb2xlIjoidXNlciIsImV4cCI6MTc3MzA1MjcwMn0.Gd1UhPRwpL4dohIH0cLjRIE18NkFIx6TDI_J_pBruvI

### Helper – obtain a fresh admin token (carol)
# Returns access_token — paste as "Bearer <token>" into @adminToken above.
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "carol@clicknback.com",
  "password": "Str0ng!Pass"
}

### Helper – obtain a fresh user token (alice)
# Returns access_token — paste as "Bearer <token>" into @userToken above.
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@clicknback.com",
  "password": "Str0ng!Pass"
}

### 200 – Happy path: list all purchases without filters (first page)
# Expected: paginated envelope with all seed purchases; total >= 6.
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchases
Authorization: {{adminToken}}

### 200 – Happy path: filter by status=confirmed
# Expected: only payments with status=confirmed (txn_seed_005 from seed data).
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchases?status=confirmed
Authorization: {{adminToken}}

### 200 – Happy path: filter by status=reversed
# Expected: only reversed purchases (txn_seed_006 from seed data).
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchases?status=reversed
Authorization: {{adminToken}}

### 200 – Happy path: filter by user_id (alice's purchases only)
# Expected: all purchases where user_id = alice's UUID.
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchases?user_id=b7e2c1a2-4f3a-4e2b-9c1a-8d2e3f4b5c6d
Authorization: {{adminToken}}

### 200 – Happy path: filter by merchant_id (Shoply purchases only)
# Expected: all purchases made at Shoply.
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchases?merchant_id=a1b2c3d4-e5f6-4a7b-8c9d-0e1f2a3b4c5d
Authorization: {{adminToken}}

### 200 – Happy path: filter by date range
# Expected: purchases with created_at between start_date and end_date (inclusive).
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchases?start_date=2026-03-02&end_date=2026-03-09
Authorization: {{adminToken}}

### 200 – Happy path: pagination — page 2, page_size 2
# Verifies offset = (2-1)*2 = 2 is applied correctly.
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchases?page=2&page_size=2
Authorization: {{adminToken}}

### 200 – Happy path: filter yields empty results
# Unknown user_id guarantees no matching rows.
# Expected: {"items": [], "total": 0, "page": 1, "page_size": 20}
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchases?user_id=00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: {{adminToken}}

### 401 – Sad path: unauthenticated request
# No Authorization header; expects 401 UNAUTHORIZED from the auth middleware.
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchases

### 401 – Sad path: authenticated as a non-admin user
# alice has role=user; this admin-only endpoint expects 401 (or 403 depending on policy).
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchases
Authorization: {{userToken}}

### 422 – Sad path: page number below minimum (page=0)
# Schema validator enforces page >= 1.
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchases?page=0
Authorization: {{adminToken}}

### 422 – Sad path: page_size exceeds maximum
# Schema validator enforces page_size <= 100 (or the configured max).
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchases?page_size=200
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
